# 13) Differential Entropy of X

h(X) = (1/2) ln(2πe)

---

# 14) Differential Entropy of Y

h(Y) = h(T) + h(P)

= (1/2)ln(2πe) + (1/2)ln(8πe)

---

# 15) Conditional Entropy h(Y|X)

h(Y|X) = h(P)
= (1/2) ln(8πe)

---

# 16) Conditional Entropy h(X|Y)

h(X|Y) = -∞

Reason: deterministic continuous variable → Dirac distribution → negative infinite entropy
